had%20to%20come%20about%20for%20people%20to%20believe%20that%20it%20was%20possible.%20It%20may%20as%20well%20have%20not%20come%20about.%20For%20years%20Rukhmabai%20had%20vacillated%20between%20fear%20and%20determination%2C%20despair%20and%20hope%2C%20uncertainty%20and%20clarity.%20She%20could%20have%20chosen%20either%20way.%20A%20different%20choice%2C%20and%20the%20world%20would%20not%20have%20heard%20her%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20like%20the%20other%20girls%2C%20she%20was%20docile%20and%20diffident.%20She%20did%20dream%20of%20getting%20educated%20and%20carving%20out%20a%20different%20kind%20of%20life%3B%20so%20would%20have%20many%20other%20girls%20of%20the%20day.%20She%20differed%20in%20that%20she%20made%20her%20life%20radically%20different.%20But%20there%20was%20nothing%20pre-ordained%20about%20it.%20Till%20very%20late%20it%20seemed%20that%20she%20might%20end%20up%20like%20the%20other%20girls.%20To%20recognize%20this%20is%20not%20to%20belittle%20Rukhmabai%E2%80%99s%20resolve%20which%20was%2C%20without%20doubt%2C%20out%20of%20the%20ordinary.%20It%20is%2C%20rather%2C%20to%20avoid%20futile%20romanticizing.%20Nothing%20is%20easier%2C%20and%20more%20tempting%2C%20than%20to%20make%20Rukhmabai%20larger%20than%20the%20objective%20forces%20around%20her.%20But%20individual%20successes%20are%20never%20entirely%20independent%20of%20historical%20constraints.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERukhmabai%20grew%20up%20in%20a%20world%20that%20was%20astir%20with%20new%20ideas.%20These%20new%20ideas%20were%20in%20clash%20with%20traditional%20beliefs%20and%20institutions.%20Reform%20and%20orthodoxy%20were%20locked%20in%20a%20bitter%20unending%20wrangle.%20It%20was%20a%20very%20complex%2C%20confusing%20and%20dynamic%20world.%20Orthodoxy%20and%20reform%2C%20old%20and%20new%2C%20progressive%20and%20reactionary%2C%20tradition%20and%20change%20were%2C%20of%20course%2C%20words%20employed%20to%20describe%20that%20world.%20They%20were%2C%20no%20less%2C%20also%20weapons%20that%20the%20rival%20groups%20hurled%20at%20one%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20326px)%2085vw%2C%20326px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F17122754%2F41a7RmaB-L.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22326%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F17122754%2F41a7RmaB-L.jpeg%20326w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F17122754%2F41a7RmaB-L-196x300.jpeg%20196w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-702058%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESudhir%20Chandra%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3ERukhmabai%3A%C2%A0The%20Life%20and%20Times%20of%20a%20Child%20Bride%20Turned%20Rebel-Doctor%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EPan%20MacMillan%20India%2C%202024%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20descriptive%20terms%2C%20they%20concealed%20as%20much%20as%20they%20revealed%20of%20that%20world.%20We%20have%20seen%20in%20the%20last%20chapter%20that%20both%20Sakharam%20and%20Ranade%20were%20proponents%20of%20reform.%20But%2C%20as%20real%20flesh-and-blood%20human%20beings%2C%20neither%20of%20them%20was%20exclusively%20new%20or%20old%2C%20reformer%20or%20reactionary.%20They%20were%20both.%20To%20further%20complicate%20things%2C%20there%20were%20varying%20ways%20in%20which%20individuals%20were%20both%20new%20and%20old%2C%20reformer%20and%20reactionary.%20Ranade%20was%20more%20new%20with%20regard%20to%20women%E2%80%99s%20education%3B%20Sakharam%20was%20more%20new%20in%20supporting%20widow%20remarriage.%20We%20have%20also%20seen%20that%20Rukhmabai%20was%20impacted%20more%20by%20Sakharam%E2%80%99s%20real-life%20ambivalences%20than%20by%20his%20categorical%20progressive%20precepts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20her%20ideas%20were%20also%20shaped%20by%20what%20she%20saw%20of%20the%20emerging%20world%20of%20social%20reform.%20This%20was%20not%20a%20distant%2C%20impersonal%20world.%20She%20was%2C%20for%20better%20and%20worse%2C%20located%20in%20the%20thick%20of%20it%20and%20felt%20simultaneously%20enthused%20and%20disillusioned%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20details%20of%20what%20she%20studied%20at%20home%20are%20not%20known.%20We%20have%20no%20idea%20of%20the%20books%2C%20newspapers%20and%20magazines%20she%20read.%20Her%20readings%2C%20probably%2C%20were%20random%20and%20miscellaneous%2C%20not%20organized%20along%20some%20kind%20of%20a%20private%20syllabus.%20She%20used%20to%20struggle%20to%20make%20sense%20of%20her%20father%E2%80%99s%20books%2C%20lectures%20and%20newspaper%20writings.%20Mohini%20Varde%20quotes%20Rukhmabai%20as%20saying%3A%20%E2%80%98I%20tried%20to%20read%20my%20father%E2%80%99s%20books%20and%20lecture%20notes%20but%20could%20understand%20very%20little.%E2%80%991%20This%20struggle%20was%20not%20confined%20to%20her%20father%E2%80%99s%20writings.%20She%20would%20also%20go%20through%20other%20texts%20that%20were%20above%20her%20level%20of%20comprehension.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20random%20readings%20apart%2C%20she%20and%20her%20half-sister%2C%20Rani%2C%20were%20often%20taken%20along%20by%20Sakharam%20to%20his%20public%20lectures.%20In%20addition%20to%20providing%20new%20information%2C%20the%20lectures%20and%20ensuing%20discussions%20would%20instil%20in%20Rukhmabai%20a%20sense%20of%20the%20culture%20and%20significance%20of%20public%20debate.%20And%2C%20of%20course%2C%20she%20had%20access%20to%20that%20unique%20source%20of%20learning%20and%20reflection%3A%20frequent%20meetings%20at%20her%20place%20of%20public%20men%2C%20writers%20and%20reformers.%20She%20would%20secretly%20imagine%20being%20like%20them%20one%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnlike%20formal%20schooling%2C%20on%20which%20Rukhmabai%20had%20lost%20out%20and%20which%20spoon-fed%20its%20beneficiaries%2C%20her%20otherwise%20cumbersome%20selfeducation%20brought%20her%20a%20special%20advantage.%20It%20obliged%20her%20to%20sift%20and%20organize%20the%20bits%20and%20fragments%20of%20miscellaneous%20information%2C%20values%20and%20ideas%20that%20she%20tirelessly%20kept%20accumulating.%20And%20this%20exercise%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20helped%20her%20forge%20her%20own%20ways%20of%20seeing%2C%20questioning%2C%20arguing%20and%20thinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%20in%20cheerless%20isolation%20was%20an%20endless%20internal%20polylogue%20for%20this%20inquisitive%20girl.%20She%20was%20quick%20to%20realize%20that%20the%20cheerlessness%20of%20her%20existence%20was%20socially%20ordained.%20It%20was%20the%20cheerlessness%20of%20all%20her%20Indian%20sisters.%20She%20was%20human%20enough%20to%20permit%20herself%20the%20comfort%20of%20self-pity%20and%20paranoia.%20But%20she%20never%20permitted%20herself%20the%20delusion%20that%20her%20suffering%20as%20a%20girl-woman%20was%20uniquely%20her%20own.%20Every%20time%20she%20provided%20an%20account%20of%20her%20life%2C%20she%20framed%20it%20within%20the%20larger%20context%20of%20the%20sisterhood.%20She%20saw%20in%20her%20own%20predicament%20a%20community%20of%20suffering%2C%20and%20in%20that%20suffering%20a%20larger%20cause%20and%20duty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFar%20and%20near%2C%20all%20around%20she%20saw%20girls%20inflicted%20by%20variations%20of%20her%20own%20unwarranted%20and%20needless%20suffering.%20Living%20next%20door%20was%20her%20best%20friend%2C%20Shanta.%20Daughter%20of%20the%20eminent%20Sanskrit%20scholar%20R.%20G.%20Bhandarkar%2C%20Shanta%20was%20eleven%20when%20she%20was%20married%20to%20the%20son%20of%20another%20prominent%20public%20figure%20of%20western%20India%2C%20Dr%20Bhau%20Daji.%20Two%20years%20later%20she%20lost%20her%20husband%2C%20and%20came%20to%20live%20with%20her%20father.%20Sorrowing%20Shanta%20and%20Rukhmabai%20began%20confiding%20in%20each%20other%20their%20intimate%20thoughts%20and%20feelings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShanta%E2%80%99s%20case%20showed%20Rukhmabai%20that%20subtle%20working%20of%20orthodoxy%20which%20virtually%20neutralized%20the%20possibility%20of%20resistance%20by%20its%20victims.%20Widow%20Shanta%20was%20fortunate%20that%20she%20was%20Bhandarkar%E2%80%99s%20daughter%20and%20Bhau%20Daji%E2%80%99s%20daughter-in-law%2C%20both%20stalwart%20reformers.%20In%201869%2C%20when%20Bombay%E2%80%99s%20first%20widow%20marriage%20was%20organized%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20Hindu%20Widow%20Remarriage%20Act%20of%201855%2C%20Bhandarkar%20was%20among%20those%20who%20defied%20organized%20Hindu%20orthodoxy%20and%20attended%20the%20wedding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhau%20Daji%20did%20something%20remarkable%20even%20earlier.%20In%201862%20a%20public%20debate%20was%20organized%20to%20resolve%20the%20question%20of%20widow%20marriage.%20Among%20the%20representatives%20of%20the%20reform%20party%20in%20the%20debate%20was%20Karsandas%20Mulji%20(1832%E2%80%9371)%2C%20one%20of%20western%20India%E2%80%99s%20pioneering%20social%20reformers.%20The%20orthodox%20party%20was%20led%20by%20Brijratanji%20Maharaja%2C%20the%20chief%20of%20a%20Vaishnava%20sect.%20The%20debate%2C%20predictably%2C%20ended%20in%20a%20deadlock.%20Thereupon%2C%20writing%20in%20his%20Satya%20Prakash%2C%20Karsandas%20charged%20that%20the%20Vaishnava%20Maharajas%20had%20%E2%80%98wilfully%20altered%20to%20their%20own%20advantage%20the%20fundamental%20rules%20and%20practices%20of%20their%20religion%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98systematically%20perverted%20their%20actual%20position%20(which%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20their%20bigoted%20followers%20is%20that%20of%20deified%20humanity)%20to%20the%20most%20gross%20and%20infamous%20debauchery%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710660607000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F17122913%2FRukhmabai.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Frukhmabai-the-quiet-making-of-a-rebel%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22For%20years%20Rukhmabai%20had%20vacillated%20between%20fear%20and%20determination%2C%20despair%20and%20hope%2C%20uncertainty%20and%20clarity.%20She%20could%20have%20chosen%20either%20way.