and%20the%20dates%20on%20which%20the%20bonds%20were%20purchased.%20The%20information%2C%20as%20expected%2C%20has%20brought%20to%20light%20potential%20%3Cem%3Equid%20pro%20quo%3C%2Fem%3E%20arrangements.%20Yet%2C%20voters%20remain%20in%20the%20dark%20about%20the%20identity%20of%20purchasers%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20more%20than%20Rs%204%2C000%20crore%20sold%20before%20April%2012%2C%202019.%20Unfortunately%2C%20the%20situation%20is%20unlikely%20to%20be%20remedied%20despite%20the%20additional%20disclosures%20that%20the%20court%20has%20directed%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20to%20make.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInterim%20order%20of%20April%2012%2C%202019%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20the%202019%20general%20elections%2C%20while%20hearing%20the%20challenge%20to%20the%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20a%20bench%20led%20by%20the%20then%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%2C%20Justice%20Ranjan%20Gogoi%2C%20observed%20that%20the%20contentions%20made%2C%20%E2%80%9Cgive%20rise%20to%20weighty%20issues%20which%20have%20a%20tremendous%20bearing%20on%20the%20sanctity%20of%20the%20electoral%20process%20in%20the%20country.%20Such%20weighty%20issues%20would%20require%20an%20in-depth%20hearing.%E2%80%9D%20In%20its%20interim%20order%20dated%20April%2012%2C%202019%2C%20although%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20refused%20to%20stay%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%2C%20the%20court%20directed%20political%20parties%20to%20submit%20information%20about%20electoral%20bonds%20received%20by%20them%20to%20the%20ECI%2C%20including%3A%20the%20details%20of%20donors%20of%20each%20bond%3B%20the%20amount%20and%20date%20of%20each%20bond%3B%20and%20details%20of%20the%20bank%20in%20which%20the%20bonds%20were%20credited.%20All%20of%20this%20was%20required%20to%20be%20submitted%20in%20a%20sealed%20cover%20by%20political%20parties%20to%20the%20ECI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWill%20the%20disclosures%20by%20the%20ECI%20make%20the%20cut%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2011%2C%202024%2C%20the%20constitution%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20directed%20the%20ECI%20to%20publish%20forthwith%20the%20information%20it%20had%20collected%20from%20political%20parties%20regarding%20bonds%20redeemed%20since%20the%20inception%20of%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ECI%20went%20back%20to%20court%20saying%20it%20could%20not%20comply%20since%20the%20original%20sealed%20envelopes%20had%20been%20submitted%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20by%20the%20ECI%20without%20keeping%20a%20copy!%20The%20Commission%20requested%20the%20SC%20to%20return%20the%20sealed%20envelopes.%20The%20court%20acceded%20to%20the%20request%20and%20gave%20time%20till%20Sunday%20(March%2017)%20for%20the%20information%20to%20be%20made%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Electoral%20Bonds%20Blow%20Giant%20Holes%20in%20Modi's%20Anti-Corruption%20Plank%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fsc-verdict-renders-pm-modis-anti-corruption-plank-shaky-amid-electoral-bond-revelations%5C%22%3EElectoral%20Bonds%20Blow%20Giant%20Holes%20in%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20Anti-Corruption%20Plank%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20629%20sealed%20envelopes%20are%20opened%20and%20their%20contents%20disclosed%2C%20we%20will%20get%20access%20to%20information%20submitted%20by%20political%20parties%20for%20all%20bonds%20redeemed%20by%20them%2C%20including%20those%20redeemed%20before%20April%2012%2C%202019.%20While%20this%20data%20is%20significant%2C%20it%20is%20unlikely%20to%20contain%20the%20names%20of%20purchasers%20%E2%80%93%20the%20holy%20grail%20of%20disclosures%2C%20which%20enable%20public%20scrutiny%20and%20tracking%20of%20%3Cem%3Equid%20pro%20quo%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20key%20element%20of%20the%20bonds%20was%20complete%20donor%20anonymity.%20As%20per%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%2C%20even%20political%20parties%20were%20not%20supposed%20to%20know%20who%20donated%20the%20bonds%20to%20them.%20Though%20it%20would%20be%20a%20reasonable%20assumption%20that%20donors%20would%20have%20found%20ways%20to%20let%20the%20recipient%20party%20know%20their%20identity%20(for%20how%20else%20would%20they%20receive%20favours%3F)%20but%20given%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20scheme%2C%20it%20would%20have%20been%20through%20informal%20channels.%20Therefore%2C%20although%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20required%20political%20parties%20to%20submit%20%E2%80%9Cdetailed%20particulars%20of%20the%20donors%20as%20against%20each%20Bond%E2%80%9D%2C%20parties%20are%20likely%20to%20have%20justifiably%20claimed%20ignorance%20and%20expressed%20their%20inability%20to%20furnish%20this%20data.%20In%20any%20case%2C%20even%20if%20donors%20revealed%20themselves%20to%20the%20recipient%20party%2C%20there%20would%20be%20no%20way%20for%20the%20party%20to%20ascertain%20whether%20the%20donor%20was%20indeed%20the%20actual%20purchaser%20of%20the%20bond.%20The%20opportunity%20that%20the%20scheme%20created%20for%20trading%20of%20bonds%20for%20a%20consideration%20with%20no%20trail%20of%20the%20transactions%2C%20opening%20the%20doors%20for%20money%20laundering%2C%20was%20also%20one%20of%20the%20grounds%20on%20which%20the%20bonds%20failed%20the%20test%20of%20constitutionality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20conclusion%2C%20even%20after%20the%20ECI%20disclosures%2C%20we%2C%20the%20people%20of%20India%2C%20are%20likely%20to%20remain%20in%20the%20dark%20about%20names%20of%20purchasers%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20over%20Rs%204%2C000%20crore%20(25%25%20of%20the%20total%20amount%20transacted%20through%20bonds).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202019%20general%20elections%2C%20people%20cast%20their%20votes%20with%20no%20information%20about%20purchasers%20and%20redeemers%20of%20electoral%20bonds.%20To%20take%20its%20landmark%20judgment%20to%20its%20logical%20conclusion%2C%20the%20court%20must%20direct%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20to%20disclose%20information%20regarding%20purchasers%20of%20bonds%20since%20the%20commencement%20of%20the%20scheme%20on%20March%201%2C%202018.%20Voters%20must%20have%20full%20details%20about%20electoral%20bonds%20to%20enable%20them%20to%20exercise%20an%20informed%20vote%20in%20the%20forthcoming%20general%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAnjali%20Bhardwaj%20and%20Amrita%20Johri%20are%20transparency%20activists%20associated%20with%20the%20National%20Campaign%20for%20Peoples%E2%80%99%20Right%20to%20Information%20and%20Satark%20Nagrik%20Sangathan.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710652094000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F17103740%2Fgst-2459328_1280.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fvoters-must-not-remain-in-the-dark-about-buyers-of-electoral-bonds-worth-rs-4000-crore%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Unfortunately%2C%20the%20situation%20is%20unlikely%20to%20be%20remedied%20despite%20the%20additional%20disclosures%20that%20the%20court%20has%20directed%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20to%20make.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fvoters-must-not-remain-in-the-dark-about-buyers-of-electoral-bonds-worth-rs-4000-crore%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kerosene%20consumption%20falls%20significantly%20by%2026%25%20CAGR%20during%20FY14-23%3A%20Data%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710651875000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-07%2F02%2Ffull%2F1688267010-605.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fkerosene-consumption-falls-significantly-by-26-cagr-during-fy14-23-data-124031700101_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Petrol%20and%20pet%20coke%20have%20witnessed%20a%20growth%20of%2013.38%20per%20cent%20and%2028.68%20per%20cent%2C%20respectively%2C%20over%20the%20last%20year.%22%2C%22au