niger-breaks-off-military-cooperation-with-us-govt%2Famp_articleshow%2F108556204.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22For%20All%20the%20Bluster%2C%20Why%20BJP%20Needs%20a%20Maha-Alliance%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F12%2F24154229%2FBJP-Jharkhand.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20talks%20of%20making%20India%20%E2%80%9Cself-reliant%E2%80%9D%20but%20is%20the%20party%20truly%20%E2%80%98atmanirbhar%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20nation%E2%80%99s%20most%20important%20state%20politically%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%3F%20It%E2%80%99s%20pertinent%20to%20ask%20this%20as%20we%20approach%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20because%20despite%20the%20myths%20created%20about%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20invincibility%20in%20the%20key%20northern%20state%2C%20which%20has%20no%20less%20than%2080%20seats%2C%20and%20the%20projection%20of%20the%20cult%20of%20Narendra%20Modi%20as%20the%20overriding%20factor%20in%20deciding%20electoral%20outcomes%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20increasingly%20needed%20outside%20help%20since%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EContrary%20to%20the%20perception%20built%20in%20mainstream%20media%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20regularly%20felt%20the%20need%20to%20rope%20in%20newer%20allies%20and%20disrupt%20Opposition%20alliances%20to%20help%20it%20sail%20through%20a%20crisis%20or%20an%20election.%20In%20fact%2C%20since%202014%2C%20the%20BJP%20under%20Modi%20has%20not%20fought%20a%20single%20election%20in%20UP%20on%20its%20own%20strength.%20As%20things%20stand%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20four%20declared%20allies%20and%20one%20supporting%20it%20from%20the%20outside.%20That%20makes%20its%20six%20parties%20in%20or%20supporting%20the%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20(NDA).%20In%20the%20real%20sense%2C%20it%20is%20the%20BJP%2C%20and%20not%20its%20rivals%2C%20Samajwadi%20Party%20or%20Congress%2C%20which%20has%20created%20a%20mahagathbandhan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20appears%20odd%20because%20the%20BJP%2C%20after%20a%20decade%20of%20rule%20at%20the%20Centre%2C%20including%20seven%20in%20Lucknow%20with%20a%20%E2%80%98double%20engine%E2%80%99%20government%2C%20claims%20to%20have%20transformed%20the%20state%20and%20developed%20it%20beyond%20recognition%20from%20a%20BIMARU%20land%20to%20one%20where%20investments%20and%20employment%20flow%20endlessly%3B%20where%20roads%2C%20highways%20and%20airports%20are%20being%20built%20at%20an%20unprecedented%20pace%3B%20where%20%3Cem%3Elabhartis%3C%2Fem%3E%20(beneficiaries)%20of%20welfare%20schemes%20are%20content%20with%20life%20and%20those%20who%2C%20especially%20Muslims%2C%20cross%20lines%20are%20punished%20with%20bulldozers%20and%20bullets.%20The%20BJP%20also%20claims%20to%20have%20struck%20a%20deathly%20blow%20to%20%E2%80%9Cappeasement%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20religion%20and%20caste%20and%20has%20presented%20the%20opening%20of%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20in%20Ayodhya%20as%20the%20greatest%20milestone%20of%20the%20Hindu%20civilisation%20in%20the%20last%20five%20centuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F22170459%2FGEb7QB7bMAA0uXA.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F22170459%2FGEb7QB7bMAA0uXA.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F22170459%2FGEb7QB7bMAA0uXA-300x185.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F22170459%2FGEb7QB7bMAA0uXA-1024x630.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-694009%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22738%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPeople%20attending%20the%20Ram%20Temple%20consecration%20ceremony%20in%20Ayodhya%20on%20January%2022%2C%202023.%20Photo%3A%20X%20(Twitter)%2FBJP4India.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20list%20is%20long.%20Here%2C%20we%20will%20trace%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20journey%20since%202014%20and%20analyse%20why%2C%20despite%20electoral%20success%20and%20claims%20of%20development%2C%20it%20is%20still%20jittery%20about%20relying%20on%20its%20own%20strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-hobbled-by-nda-trouble-and-struggle-in-key-states%5C%22%3EBJP%20Hobbled%20by%20NDA%20Trouble%20(and%20Struggle)%20in%20Key%20States%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20chief%20minister%20Yogi%20Adityanath%20carried%20out%20the%20much-awaited%20expansion%20of%20his%20cabinet.%20He%20inducted%20four%20new%20faces.%20Two%20of%20them%20belong%20to%20newly-added%20allies%20of%20the%20BJP%2C%20Om%20Prakash%20Rajbhar%20(president%20of%20the%20Suheldev%20Bharatiya%20Samaj%20Party%20who%20returned%20to%20the%20saffron%20fold)%20and%20Anil%20Kumar%20(of%20Jayant%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20Rashtriya%20Lok%20Dal).%20With%20the%20addition%20of%20a%20Dalit%2C%20Brahmin%20and%20two%20OBCs%20(Rajbhar%20and%20Noniya%20Chauhan)%20as%20ministers%2C%20the%20saffron%20party%20balanced%20caste%20equations%20but%20also%20accommodated%20its%20new%20allies%20in%20the%20ministries.%20This%20has%20been%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20trend%20in%20the%20state%20since%202014%2C%20when%20it%20emerged%20as%20a%20dominant%20force.%20The%20party%20has%20won%20back-to-back%20majorities%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20state%20Assembly%20elections%20and%20cornered%20over%2090%25%20and%2080%25%20of%20the%20seats%20in%20the%20last%20two%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUndeniably%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20credit%20goes%20to%20the%20appeal%20of%20Modi%2C%20his%20superior%20communication%20skills%2C%20disruptive%20politics%20and%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20management%20of%20large%20sections%20of%20the%20media%20to%20convert%20every%20%3Cem%3Eaapda%3C%2Fem%3E%20into%20an%20%3Cem%3Eausar%3C%2Fem%3E%20(disaster%20into%20an%20opportunity)%20to%20attract%20votes.%20The%20BJP%20has%20also%20displayed%20superior%20strategies%20and%20narratives%20to%20polarise%20votes%20on%20caste%20and%20religious%20lines%20and%20manipulated%20Hindu%20sentiments%2C%20while%20attributing%20its%20own%20success%20to%20the%20dissemination%20of%20welfare%20schemes%20on%20the%20ground.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20lacklustre%20Opposition%20parties%20have%20been%20constantly%20battling%20their%20collective%20political%20baggage%2C%20squabbling%20with%20each%20other%20over%20petty%20issues%2C%20and%20facing%20attacks%20and%20raids%20by%20central%20and%20state%20agencies.%20The%20Bahujan%20Samaj%20Party%2C%20through%20its%20seemingly%20neutral%20stance%2C%20has%20also%20benefited%20the%20incumbent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20sum%2C%20the%20BJP%20looks%20to%20be%20in%20a%20dominant%20position.%20Why%20does%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20party%20then%20need%20the%20support%20of%20smaller%20caste-centric%20political%20parties%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20possible%20answers%20for%20it.%20One%2C%20the%20BJP%20simply%20thinks%20it%20cannot%20perform%20so%20well%20on%20its%20own.%20It%20cannot%20ignore%20the%20aspirations%20of%20smaller%20backward%20caste-based%20parties%20that%20have%20emerged%20in%20the%20post-Mandal%20era%20because%20at%20its%20core%20it%20is%20still%20dominated%20by%20the%20so-called%20Upper%20Castes%20and%20viewed%20as%20one%20that%20furthers%20their%20politics.%20To%20sustain%20the%20support%20of%20these%20OBC%20communities%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%20the%20party%20needs%20to%20appropriate%20their%20leaders.%20Modi%20might%20project%20himself%20as%20an%20OBC%20but%20the%20BJP%20understands%20that%20in%20the%20core%20Hindi%20belt%2C%20it%20will%20also%20have%20to%20appease%20regional%20caste%20satraps%20and%20promote%20credible%2C%20independent%20faces%20from%20within%20these%20communities.%20With%20the%20centralisation%20of%20power%20in%20the%20BJP%2C%20this%20becomes%20even%20more%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20explanation%20could%20be%20that%20the%20BJP%20is%20confident%20about%20winning%20but%20wants%20to%20gain%20territory%20further%20or%20at%20least%20retain%20what%20it%20has.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it%20wants%20to%20shut%20out%20possibilities%20of%20the%20main%20Opposition%20building%20a%20counter-narrative%20with%20the%20help%20of%20these%20smaller%20parties.%20It%20is%20not%20just%20about%20arithmetic%20but%20the%20expansion%20of%20its%20political%20hegemony%20in%20the%20post-Modi%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20explanations%20have%20merit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20pattern%20of%20tactical%20opportunism%20took%20shape%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202014.%20It%20was%20remarkable%20that%20the%20BJP%2C%20which%20was%20banking%20on%20the%20so-called%20%E2%80%98Modi%20wave%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20Gujarat%20Model%20of%20Hindu%20polarisation%20and%20development%20and%20the%20glorious%20dreams%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EAche%20Din%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20still%20needed%20an%20ally%20in%20that%20election.%20In%202014%2C%20when%20all%20the%20other%20Opposition%20parties%20contested%20individually%2C%20the%20BJP%20allied%20with%20the%20Apna%20Dal%2C%20a%20political%20minnow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20noteworthy%20is%20that%20the%20Apna%20Dal%2C%20which%20had%20just%20a%20single%20MLA%20in%20the%20UP%20Assembly%2C%20got%20two%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20(which%20equates%20to%2010%20Assembly%20constituencies)%20as%20part%20of%20the%20deal.%20One%20of%20the%20seats%2C%20Mirzapur%2C%20abuts%20Varanasi%2C%20from%20where%20Modi%20contested.%20The%20benevolence%20was%20well-thought%20out%2C%20as%20it%20not%20only%20sent%20a%20positive%20signal%20to%20the%20Kurmi%20OBC%20community%2C%20the%20core%20base%20of%20the%20Apna%20Dal%20in%20Varanasi%20and%20Prayagraj%20belts%2C%20but%20more%20importantly%20ensured%20a%20smoother%20ride%20for%20Modi%20in%20Varanasi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnupriya%20Patel%2C%20today%20a%20minister%20in%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20government%2C%20was%20the%20sole%20Apna%20Dal%20MLA%20in%202014.%20She%20held%20the%20Rohaniya%20seat%2C%20one%20of%20the%20five%20that%20constitute%20the%20Varanasi%20Lok%20Sabha%20constituency.%20What%20made%20things%20interesting%20was%20that%20she%20had%20expressed%20her%20desire%20to%20contest%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20from%20Varanasi.%20Had%20she%20taken%20the%20leap%2C%20things%20would%20have%20become%20complicated%20for%20Modi%20because%20two%20out%20of%20the%20three%20constituents%20of%20Varanasi%20LS%20are%20rural%20and%20packed%20with%20Kurmi%20voters.%20Modi%20was%20already%20facing%20the%20challenge%20of%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20convenor%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%20and%20also%20in%20the%20fray%20were%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99%20RSS-bred%20candidate%20and%20five-time%20MLA%20Ajay%20Rai%2C%20and%20candidates%20from%20the%20SP%20and%20the%20BSP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F07%2FAnupriya_Patel_Modi_PTI_3x2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Anupriya%20Patel%20with%20Narendra%20Modi.%20Credit%3A%20PTI%2FFiles%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F07%2FAnupriya_Patel_Modi_PTI_3x2.jpg%20600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F07%2FAnupriya_Patel_Modi_PTI_3x2-300x200.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-49663%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22401%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAnupriya%20Patel%20with%20Narendra%20Modi.%20Credit%3A%20PTI%2FFiles%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20had%20to%20ensure%20a%20smooth%20transfer%20of%20OBC%20votes%20to%20supplement%20its%20core%20urban%20vote%20base.%20Modi%20eventually%20defeated%20Kejriwal%20by%20over%203.71%20lakh%20votes.%20The%20Apna%20Dal%20won%20two%20seats%2C%20including%20Mirzapur%20(Anupriya%20Patel%20was%20the%20winner)%2C%20which%20abuts%20the%20rural%20areas%20of%20Varanasi.%20The%20BJP%20won%2071%20seats%2C%20giving%20the%20NDA%2073%20out%20of%2080%20seats.%20The%20BJP%20was%20successful%20in%20marketing%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98chai%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98cup%20and%20saucer%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20Apna%20Dal%20(its%20election%20symbol).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20journey%20in%20UP%20in%20the%20Modi%20era%20has%20not%20been%20a%20linear%2C%20vertical%20line%20but%20one%20full%20of%20experiments%20and%20timely%20alliances%2C%20with%20the%20sole%20intent%20of%20polarising%20voters%20and%20increasing%20vote%20share%20at%20any%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20major%20challenge%20came%20in%202017%2C%20when%20the%20BJP%20battled%20a%20perception%20that%2C%20while%20it%20had%20won%20the%20general%20election%20with%20Modi%20as%20Prime%20Ministerial%20face%20banking%20on%20a%20national%20campaign%20against%20Congress%2C%20it%20would%20be%20a%20different%20game%20in%20the%20Assembly%20election.%20UP%20had%20rotated%20powers%20between%20the%20SP%20and%20BSP%20for%20the%20last%20three%20terms.%20The%20BJP%20lagged%20in%20the%20third%20position%20in%20the%20State%20Assembly%20with%2015%25%20votes%20and%20lacked%20a%20CM%20face%20with%20pan-UP%20acceptability%20or%20caste%20appeal%20and%20formula%20to%20match%20Mayawati%20or%20Akhilesh%20Yadav.%20To%20put%20itself%20in%20the%20picture%2C%20the%20BJP%20dismantled%20the%20main%20Opposition%20and%20contender%20BSP%20by%20luring%20away%20its%20leaders%20and%20MLAs%20and%20through%20demonetisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeven%20months%20before%20the%202017%20election%2C%20Amit%20Shah%20decided%20it%20was%20time%20to%20add%20another%20ally%20to%20push%20the%20narrative%20of%20non-Yadav%20OBC%20vs%20Yadavs%20and%20corner%20the%20controversy-ridden%20Akhilesh%20Yadav%20government.%20The%20second%20ally%20was%20the%20Suheldev%20Bharatiya%20Samaj%20Party%2C%20formed%20in%202002%20by%20former%20BSP%20leader%20Om%20Prakash%20Rajbhar.%20The%20SBSP%20did%20not%20have%20a%20single%20MLA%20in%20UP%20back%20then%20even%20though%20it%20enjoyed%20the%20support%20of%20a%20section%20of%20Rajbhar%2C%20Arakhs%20and%20Bhars%20in%20the%20Ghazipur-Mau%20belt%20of%20Purvanchal.%20What%20made%20the%20SBSP%20more%20attractive%20was%20that%20for%20many%20years%20the%20Sangh%20Parivar%20has%20projected%20Suheldev%2C%20a%20mythical%20Bhar%20chieftain%20after%20whom%20the%20party%20is%20named%2C%20as%20a%20crusader%20against%20Islam%20and%20one%20who%20allegedly%20stopped%20the%20march%20of%20Salar%20Masud%20%E2%80%98Ghazi%20Mian%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20nephew%20of%20Mahmud%20Ghaznavi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F16174736%2F327768460_572311678263377_8560959012336237590_n.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F16174736%2F327768460_572311678263377_8560959012336237590_n.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F16174736%2F327768460_572311678263377_8560959012336237590_n-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F16174736%2F327768460_572311678263377_8560959012336237590_n-1024x684.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-702017%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22801%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EOP%20Rajbhar.%20Photo%3A%20Facebook%2FOm%20Prakash%20Rajbhar%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20propagating%20Suheldev%E2%80%99s%20fable%20through%20a%20Hindutva%20lens%2C%20the%20BJP%20tried%20to%20pit%20Bhars%20and%20Pasis%20(a%20Dalit%20community%20that%20also%20claims%20ownership%20of%20the%20legacy%20of%20Suheldev)%20against%20Muslims.%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20since%20coming%20to%20power%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20tried%20to%20further%20popularise%20Suheldev%20and%20dedicated%20memorials%2C%20stamps%2C%20a%20university%20and%20a%20superfast%20train%20from%20Ghazipur%20to%20Delhi%20to%20him.%20While%20inducting%20the%20SBSP%20into%20the%20alliance%2C%20the%20BJP%2C%20which%20harps%20about%20a%20no-tolerance%20policy%20against%20tainted%20politicians%2C%20ignored%20the%20fact%20that%20Rajbhar%20had%20in%202014%20aligned%20with%20the%20party%20of%20jailed%20MLA%20Mukhtar%20Ansari%2C%20whom%20the%20saffron%20party%20refers%20to%20as%20a%20mafia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%E2%80%99s%202017%20campaign%20was%20a%20success%20as%20it%20defeated%20an%20incompatible%20alliance%20of%20the%20SP%20and%20Congress.%20The%20BSP%2C%20the%20main%20Opposition%20party%20in%202012%2C%20was%20reduced%20to%2019%20seats.%20The%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20alliance%20with%20the%20Apna%20Dal%20and%20the%20SBSP%20provided%20mutual%20benefits%20to%20all%20sides%20and%20further%20helped%20the%20BJP%20script%20a%20narrative%20that%20while%20the%20SP%20stood%20only%20for%20Yadavs%2C%20it%20was%20the%20voice%20of%20the%20remaining%20OBCs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20backward%20castes%20are%20the%20most%20important%20voting%20segment%20in%20UP%20estimated%20to%20be%20around%2045-50%25%20of%20the%20electorate.%20The%20NDA%20won%20a%20thumping%20majority%E2%80%94325%20seats%20in%20the%20403-member%20Assembly.%20The%20Apna%20Dal%20grew%20further%20and%20increased%20its%20MLA%20tally%20from%20one%20to%20nine.%20The%20SBSP%20made%20a%20debut%20in%20the%20Assembly%2C%20winning%20four%20seats.%20Rajbhar%20was%20rewarded%20with%20a%20cabinet%20minister%20berth.%20Interestingly%2C%20both%20Apna%20Dal%20and%20SBSP%20can%20trace%20their%20origins%20to%20Kanshiram%E2%80%99s%20BSP.%20While%20Apnal%20Dal%20founder%20and%20Anupriya%20Patel%E2%80%99s%20father%2C%20Sone%20Lal%20Patel%20was%20a%20founding%20member%20of%20the%20BSP%2C%20Rajbhar%20was%20also%20an%20office-bearer%20before%20he%20broke%20off%20ties%20after%20differences%20with%20Mayawati.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20election%20win%2C%20however%2C%20presented%20the%20BJP%20with%20a%20quandary%20on%20whom%20to%20pick%20as%20CM.%20The%20party%20finally%20settled%20on%20planting%20Yogi%20Adityanath%2C%20then%20Gorakhpur%20MP%2C%20as%20the%20head%20of%20government%20in%20Lucknow.%20Adityanath%E2%80%99s%20saffron%20identity%20gave%20him%20a%20strong%20Hindutva%20persona%20and%20the%20ambiguity%20to%20downplay%20his%20upper%20caste%20identity%20to%20balance%20the%20aspirations%20of%20both%20upper%20castes%20and%20backward%20castes.%20With%20a%20monk%20espousing%20Hindutva%20at%20the%20helm%2C%20the%20BJP%20would%20not%20face%20the%20same%20pressure%20it%20would%20had%20it%20picked%20a%20Brahmin%20as%20CM%20(which%20would%20have%20antagonised%20OBCs)%20or%20an%20OBC%20(which%20would%20have%20irked%20the%20dominant%20and%20influential%20Brahmin%20lobby%20which%20has%20a%20disproportionate%20representation%20in%20judiciary%2C%20bureaucracy%20and%20media).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdityanath%20offered%20them%20the%20balance.%20However%2C%20things%20did%20not%20go%20as%20per%20plan%20as%20the%20BJP%20and%20SBSP%20relationship%20started%20to%20show%20strains%20after%20Rajbhar%20took%20on%20his%20own%20government%2C%20often%20making%20unsavoury%20comments%20and%20demanding%20the%20sub-categorisation%20of%20the%20OBC%20quota.%20Rajbhar%20even%20exhorted%20his%20supporters%20to%20thrash%20BJP%20members.%20A%20helpful%20OBC%20ally%20in%202017%2C%20he%20had%20now%20turned%20into%20a%20hot%20potato%20for%20the%20BJP.%20But%20despite%20the%20provocation%20by%20Rajbhar%2C%20who%20even%20fielded%20rebel%20candidates%20against%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%2C%20the%20saffron%20party%20did%20not%20take%20any%20disciplinary%20action%20against%20him%20and%20tried%20to%20appease%20him%20till%20the%20last%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20sacked%20him%20as%20minister%20only%20after%20voting%20concluded%2C%20demonstrating%20that%20it%20did%20fear%20repercussions%20of%20acting%20against%20him%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202019%20election%2C%20the%20BJP%20under%20Modi%20was%20facing%20its%20greatest%20ever%20challenge%20from%20the%20grand%20alliance%20of%20the%20SP%2C%20BSP%20and%20RLD.%20The%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20ally%20Apna%20Dal%2C%20which%20was%20unhappy%20with%20the%20proposed%20division%20of%20the%20OBC%20quota%20by%20the%20Adityanath%20government%2C%20saw%20this%20as%20an%20opportunity%20to%20demand%20more%20seats%20from%20its%20ally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20even%20as%20the%20pressure%20was%20building%20on%20the%20BJP%20from%20both%20allies%2C%20the%20Apna%20Dal%20fell%20in%20line%20due%20to%20the%20atmosphere%20of%20charged%20nationalism%20following%20the%20Pulwama%20attack%20and%20tension%20with%20Pakistan.%20The%20BJP%20still%20had%20to%20compensate%20for%20the%20loss%20of%20Rajbhar.%20They%20found%20the%20alternative%20in%20another%20OBC%20leader%20Sanjay%20Nishad%2C%20president%20of%20the%20Nishad%20Party%20which%20claims%20to%20represent%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20fisherfolk%20and%20riverine%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F04%2F29144438%2F278292233_3217286848555921_83924186085448989_n.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22959%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F04%2F29144438%2F278292233_3217286848555921_83924186085448989_n.jpg%20959w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F04%2F29144438%2F278292233_3217286848555921_83924186085448989_n-300x163.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-594481%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22521%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESanjay%20Nishad.%20Photo%3A%20Facebook%2FNISHAD%20Party%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20it%20was%20Sanjay%20Nishad%E2%80%99s%20son%20Praveen%20Nishad%20who%2C%20contesting%20as%20an%20SP%20candidate%2C%20had%20defeated%20the%20BJP%20in%20a%20by-poll%20in%20the%20saffron%20party%E2%80%99s%20bastion%20Gorakhpur.%20Akhilesh%20Yadav%20hoped%20to%20replicate%20this%20formula%20in%202019%20as%20the%20SP-BSP-RLD%20alliance%20was%20joined%20by%20the%20Nishad%20Party.%20While%20joining%20the%20anti-BJP%20front%2C%20Sanjay%20Nishad%20promised%20to%20fight%20the%20battle%20of%2085%20vs%2015%20(OBCs%20and%20Dalits%20vs%20the%20UCs).%20However%2C%20within%20a%20week%20of%20that%20agreement%2C%20the%20BJP%2C%20sensing%20trouble%2C%20managed%20to%20lure%20him%20away%20to%20its%20camp.%20The%20turn%20was%20so%20sharp%20that%20now%2C%20Sanjay%20Nishad%20described%20his%20alliance%20with%20the%20BJP%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnatural%20one%E2%80%9D%20based%20on%20the%20bond%20between%20Lord%20Ram%20and%20Nishadraj%2C%20the%20boatman%20who%20ferried%20the%20former%20across%20the%20Ganga%20in%20the%20Ramayana.%20The%20Nishads%2C%20known%20by%20their%20various%20sub-castes%20such%20as%20Mallahs%2C%20Kewat%2C%20Kashyap%20and%20Bind%2C%20are%20spread%20across%20the%20state.%20Bandit-turned-politician%20Phoolan%20Devi%20was%20among%20their%20most%20iconic%20figures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20social%20arithmetic%20of%20Hindu%20castes%2C%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20appeal%2C%20internal%20contradictions%20between%20the%20SP%20and%20BSP%2C%20and%20a%20high-pitched%20campaign%20on%20Hindu%20nationalism%20were%20among%20the%20factors%20that%20helped%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20Apna%20Dal%20win%2064%20out%20of%2080%20seats.%20The%20Apnal%20Dal%20won%20two.%20Sanjay%20Nishad%E2%80%99s%20son%20won%20on%20a%20BJP%20symbol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESmaller%20caste-based%20parties%20such%20as%20the%20Apna%20Dal%2C%20SBSP%20and%20Nishad%20Party%20find%20it%20difficult%20to%20win%20seats%20on%20their%20own%20strength.%20However%2C%20when%20their%20scattered%20support%20bases%20are%20added%20to%20a%20larger%20party%2C%20such%20as%20the%20BJP%20demonstrated%20in%202017%20and%202019%2C%20the%20result%20is%20a%20mutually%20beneficial%20one.%20This%20was%20the%20trick%20Akhilesh%20picked%20up%20and%20tried%20to%20implement%20in%20the%202022%20Assembly%20election.%20In%20the%20last%20three%20decades%2C%20UP%20had%20developed%20a%20trend%20of%20voting%20out%20the%20incumbent%20and%20this%20was%20the%20challenge%20Adityanath%20faced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20alliances%20change%20the%20overall%20contest%20was%20demonstrated%20in%20the%202022%20election.%20Though%20the%20BJP%20and%20its%20allies%20AD%20and%20Nishad%20Party%20scripted%20a%20historic%20win%2C%20winning%20273%20seats%20with%20over%2043%25%20votes%2C%20the%20Opposition%20alliance%20of%20the%20SP%20and%20smaller-caste%20based%20parties%20including%20the%20SBSP%2C%20RLD%20and%20the%20Apna%20Dal%20(Kameravadi)%2C%20the%20faction%20of%20the%20AD%20led%20by%20Anupriya%20Patel%E2%80%99s%20mother%20after%20she%20split%20from%20the%20BJP%2C%20put%20up%20a%20decent%20fight.%20The%20rainbow%20alliance%20of%20Akhilesh%20Yadav%20built%20on%20providing%20OBC%20castes%20their%20share%20in%20power%20won%20125%20seats%20with%20a%20decent%20vote%20share%20of%20around%2036%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhat-might-the-congress-samajwadi-party-alliance-achieve-in-uttar-pradesh%5C%22%3EWhat%20Might%20the%20Congress-Samajwadi%20Party%20Alliance%20Achieve%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20importantly%2C%20the%20alliance%20with%20OBC%20parties%20allowed%20the%20SP%20to%20shed%20the%20image%20of%20a%20party%20that%20only%20caters%20to%20Yadavs%20and%20started%20to%20develop%20a%20counter-narrative%20to%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20mobilisation%20of%20OBCs%20and%20Dalits.%20In%202017%2C%20the%20SP%20had%20won%20just%2047%20seats.%20The%20collective%20vote%20of%20the%20SP%2C%20RLD%20and%20the%20SBSP%2C%20and%20the%20support%20of%20other%20allied%20parties%2C%20touching%2036%25%20was%20significant.%20In%20the%202012%20and%202017%20elections%2C%20when%20the%20SP%20and%20the%20BJP%20secured%20majorities%2C%20they%20got%2029.15%25%20and%2039.67%25%20votes%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202022%20election%20result%20provided%20the%20BJP%20a%20glimpse%20of%20what%20challenges%20it%20could%20face%20in%20future.%20In%20Purvanchal%2C%20where%20the%20SP%E2%80%99s%20alliances%20were%20potent%2C%20the%20BJP%20scored%20a%20zero%20in%20many%20important%20districts%20despite%20large%20populations%20of%20Dalits%20and%20OBCs.%20For%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20allies%2C%20the%202022%20election%20proved%20beneficial.%20The%20AD%20increased%20its%20tally%20to%2013%20MLAs%20while%20the%20Nishad%20Party%20won%20six%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Akhilesh%20Yadav%E2%80%99s%20equations%20did%20not%20sustain%20after%20the%20defeat.%20Months%20after%20the%20result%2C%20Rajbhar%20broke%20off%20ties%20with%20the%20SP%20and%20after%20spending%20some%20time%20in%20the%20wilderness%2C%20joined%20the%20saffron%20camp%20again%20last%20year.%20Despite%20an%20acrimonious%20relationship%20during%20their%20last%20tenure%2C%20and%20Rajbhar%20making%20derogatory%20personal%20remarks%20against%20Adityanath%20and%20Modi%2C%20the%20BJP%20welcomed%20him%20back%20when%20it%20could%20have%20displayed%20moral%20courage%20and%20kept%20him%20at%20a%20distance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20was%20shaping%20up%20to%20be%20another%20grand%20battle%20between%20two%20alliances%2C%20INDIA%20bloc%20vs%20NDA%2C%20till%20the%20BJP%20managed%20to%20wean%20away%20the%20RLD.%20The%20RLD%20chief%20Chaudhary%20Jayant%20Singh%2C%20who%20had%20spent%20a%20decade%20fighting%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20communal%20agenda%20in%20the%20volatile%20western%20region%20of%20the%20state%2C%20made%20the%20switch%20public%20on%20a%20day%20when%20the%20Modi%20government%20announced%20a%20Bharat%20Ratna%20for%20his%20grandfather%2C%20former%20PM%20Chaudhary%20Charan%20Singh.%20The%20RLD%20even%20settled%20for%20a%20lesser%20number%20of%20seats%2C%20two%2C%20as%20against%20the%20seven%20it%20had%20got%20under%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20agreement%2C%20as%20it%20joined%20the%20NDA%20and%20subsequently%20earned%20a%20ministerial%20berth%20in%20the%20Adityanath%20cabinet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhat-does-om-prakash-rajbhars-return-to-nda-mean-for-up-politics%5C%22%3EWhat%20Does%20Om%20Prakash%20Rajbhar%E2%80%99s%20Return%20to%20NDA%20Mean%20for%20UP%20Politics%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20sweeping%20most%20of%20the%20seats%20in%20the%20west%2C%20the%20BJP%20must%20have%20been%20wary%20of%20the%20potential%20of%20a%20growing%20camaraderie%20between%20the%20SP%20and%20the%20RLD%2C%20which%20provided%20the%20agrarian%20population%20in%20the%20western%20region%20an%20alternate%20electoral%20equation%20against%20the%20BJP.%20Therefore%2C%20despite%20dealing%20with%20a%20problem%20of%20plenty%20in%20sharing%20power%20with%20its%20allies%2C%20the%20BJP%20was%20more%20than%20happy%20to%20break%20the%20SP-RLD%20alliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20has%20already%20saturated%20its%20success%20ratio%20in%20the%20west.%20It%20outmuscled%20the%20Opposition%20in%202019%20despite%20the%20combined%20strength%20of%20the%20SP-BSP-RLD.%C2%A0%20Therefore%2C%20the%20argument%20that%20the%20party%20inducted%20the%20RLD%20to%20retain%20its%20ground%20amid%20possible%20anti-incumbency%20is%20only%20half%20the%20story.%20The%20alliance%20will%20not%20help%20the%20BJP%20win%20any%20more%20seats%20than%20it%20did%20in%202019.%20The%20larger%20motive%20appears%20to%20be%20to%20reduce%20hostility%20in%20a%20region%20where%20the%20party%2C%20with%20the%20co-option%20of%20the%20RLD%2C%20would%20have%20little%20opposition.%20Ever%20since%20the%202013%20Muzaffarnagar%20riots%2C%20the%20Hindus%2C%20especially%20Jats%2C%20in%20several%20districts%20have%20been%20hostile%20to%20the%20SP.%20The%20RLD%20was%20the%20SP%E2%80%99s%20bridge%20into%20the%20sugarcane-rich%20west.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20not%20only%20wants%20to%20consolidate%20what%20it%20has%20gained%20since%202014%20but%20also%20wants%20to%20prevent%20any%20counter-mobilisation%20of%20the%20Opposition%20and%20knows%20when%20to%20deliver%20psychological%20blows.%20An%20SP-RLD%20alliance%20in%20the%20west%20and%20an%20SP-SBSP%20alliance%20in%20the%20east%20would%20have%20definitely%20posed%20the%20saffron%20party%20bigger%20challenges%20in%20the%20present%20and%20future.%20By%20luring%20in%20Opposition%20parties%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20also%20once%20again%20isolated%20the%20main%20Opposition%20SP%20and%20tried%20to%20project%20it%20as%20one%20that%20cannot%20be%20trusted%20as%20an%20ally.%20In%20fact%2C%20this%20narrative%20was%20placed%20in%20the%20Assembly%20earlier%20this%20year%20by%20Adityanath%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20long%20run%2C%20by%20providing%20a%20share%20in%20power%20to%20these%20smaller%20allies%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20created%20a%20favourable%20ground%20to%20build%20a%20relationship%20with%20their%20support%20bases%20and%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20appropriate%20their%20icons%20Charan%20Singh%2C%20Sonelal%20Patel%2C%20Nishadraj%20and%20Suheldev.%20The%20upcoming%20election%20results%20will%20determine%20how%20that%20takes%20shape.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710638995000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F12%2F24154229%2FBJP-Jharkhand.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%