cies%20for%20alleged%20money%20laundering%20by%20these%20entities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQuoting%20sources%20in%20the%20FIU%20then%2C%20a%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Farticle%2Fpti-stories%2Fgovt-publishes-names-of-9-500-high-risk-nbfcs-118022600622_1.html%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20had%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20activities%20of%20these%20institutions%20%E2%80%93%20post%20the%20demonetisation%20of%20large%20currency%20notes%20of%20Rs%201%2C000%20and%20Rs%20500%20in%20November%202016%20%E2%80%93%20were%20under%20the%20scanner%20of%20the%20FIU%20and%20it%20published%20their%20names%20after%20analysing%20their%20data%20from%20various%20information%20sources.%E2%80%9D%20A%20senior%20ministry%20official%20had%20told%20the%20newspaper%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20publication%20of%20this%20information%20in%20newspapers%20is%20primarily%20a%20step%20by%20the%20FIU%20to%20make%20aware%20the%20public%20that%20these%20NBFCs%20are%20not%20law%20compliant%20and%20that%20they%20should%20refrain%20from%20indulging%20into%20transactions%20with%20them.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFIU%2C%20since%2C%20then%2C%20has%20been%20putting%20out%20an%20annual%20list%20of%20non-banking%20financial%20companies%20(NBFCs)%20that%20have%20not%20complied%20with%20the%20rules%20of%20PMLA%2C%20and%20thereby%20alerting%20the%20enforcement%20agencies%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESignificantly%2C%20thorough%20scrutiny%20of%20the%20ECI%E2%80%99s%20list%20by%20The%20Wire%20holds%20up%20that%20all%20the%2019%20companies%20marked%20%E2%80%98high%20risk%E2%80%99%20by%20the%20FIU%20that%20have%20gone%20on%20to%20buy%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20belong%20to%20the%202018%20list%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBought%20Bond%20and%20off%20FIU%20List%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20as%20many%20as%2018%20of%20these%2019%20companies%20that%20had%20bought%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20coincidentally%20did%20not%20appear%20in%20the%20FIU%E2%80%99s%20subsequent%20annual%20lists%20of%20%E2%80%98high%20risk%E2%80%99%20NBFCs.%20So%20only%20one%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98high%20risk%E2%80%99%20companies%20which%20we%20found%20to%20have%20bought%20bonds%2C%20remained%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98high%20risk%E2%80%99%20entity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWeeks%20after%20the%202018%20list%20was%20put%20out%20by%20the%20FIU%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Farticle%2Fpti-stories%2Fover-1-200-nbfcs-submit-records-to-govt-after-being-called-non-compliant-officials-118041900699_1.html%5C%22%3Ea%20PTI%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20quoting%20Ministry%20of%20Finance%20officials%2C%20had%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cover%201200%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%209%2C491%20companies%20named%20in%20the%202018%20%E2%80%98high%20risk%E2%80%99%20list%20had%20filed%20additional%20documents%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20rules%20of%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%20(PMLA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERenuka%20Investment%20Finance%20Limited%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20that%20has%20continued%20to%20feature%20in%20the%20Ministry%E2%80%99s%20subsequent%20lists%20of%20%E2%80%98high%20risk%E2%80%99%20NBFCs%20is%20Renuka%20Investment%20Finance%20Limited.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERegistered%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%E2%80%99s%20Sonbhadra%2C%20Renuka%20Investment%20Finance%20Limited%20had%20featured%20in%20the%20FIU%E2%80%99s%20annual%20%E2%80%98high-risk%E2%80%99%20list%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffiuindia.gov.in%2Fpdfs%2Fquicklinks%2FHigh%2520Risk%2520NBFCs%2520updated.pdf%5C%22%3E2018%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffiuindia.gov.in%2Fpdfs%2Fquicklinks%2FNon_compliant_NBFCs-Non_registration_of_PO31032019.pdf%5C%22%3E2019%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffiuindia.gov.in%2Fpdfs%2Fquicklinks%2FNonCompliantNBFC23072021.pdf%5C%22%3E2021%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffiuindia.gov.in%2Fpdfs%2Fquicklinks%2FNonCompliantNBFC16032022.