5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EParticipants%20displaying%20the%20popular%20food%20items%20from%20their%20tribal%20communities%20at%20the%20stalls%20in%20Samvaad.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Cuisine%20connects%20us%20with%20the%20outside%20world%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFood%20is%20central%20to%20one%E2%80%99s%20sense%20of%20identity%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F344526%2Fsamvaad-tata-steel-foundation-celebrates-culture-of-tribes-of-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplays%20an%20integral%20role%20at%20Samvaad%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Every%20ingredient%2C%20be%20it%20vegetable%2C%20fruit%2C%20or%20spice%2C%20used%20in%20a%20dish%20represents%20a%20community%E2%80%99s%20biology%20and%20sociology%2C%20and%20forms%20a%20larger%20part%20of%20its%20historical%20narrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20spoke%20to%20chefs%20from%20different%20parts%20of%20India%20and%20even%20got%20an%20opportunity%20to%20relish%20some%20of%20their%20food%20at%20Gopal%20Maidan.%20Despite%20the%20difference%20in%20their%20preparation%20styles%20and%20ingredients%20used%2C%20something%20unified%20the%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20Vasantha%20from%20the%20Irula%20tribe%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%20said%20%3Cem%3Eragi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(finger%20millet)%20is%20the%20primary%20cereal%20in%20her%20village.%20They%20use%20it%20to%20make%20%3Cem%3Edosa%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3Eragi%20%3C%2Fem%3Eballs.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Santi%20Bairak%20from%20the%20Chik%20Baraik%20tribe%20of%20Odisha%20uses%20%3Cem%3Eragi%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20make%20fritters%2C%20%3Cem%3Esamosa%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Emanchurian%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20even%20milkshakes.%20Then%20there%20is%20also%20Swati%20from%20the%20Oraon%20tribe%20who%20makes%20%3Cem%3Eragi%3C%2Fem%3E%20cakes%20and%20pastries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20taste%20of%20their%20dishes%20%E2%80%94%20umami%2C%20spicy%20and%20sweet%20%E2%80%94%20are%20poles%20apart%2C%20the%20reason%20for%20using%20%3Cem%3Eragi%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20the%20same%20%E2%80%94%20health%20benefits%20and%20easy%20access.%20And%20it%20got%20more%20interesting%20when%20Vasantha%20took%20a%20leaf%20out%20of%20Santi%E2%80%99s%20culinary%20book%2C%20went%20back%20home%2C%20and%20experimented%20with%20it!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Vasantha%2C%20Santi%20and%20other%20chefs%2C%20their%20role%20goes%20beyond%20cooking%20and%20showcasing%20their%20food%3B%20it%20is%20a%20way%20to%20connect%20their%20community%20with%20the%20outside%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFood%20is%20actually%20the%20easiest%20way%20to%20initiate%20a%20conversation%20with%20strangers.%20However%2C%20though%20people%20may%20connect%20via%20%3Cem%3EPunjabi%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EGujarati%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20Goan%20cuisine%2C%20rarely%20are%20they%20aware%20of%20tribal%20cuisine.%20Part%20of%20the%20problem%20is%20the%20blanket%20labelling%20of%20tribal%20foods%20under%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98indigenous%E2%80%99%2C%20when%20in%20fact%20our%20food%20is%20as%20diverse%20as%20it%20can%20get.%20So%2C%20when%20people%20visit%20my%20stall%2C%20I%20make%20sure%20to%20educate%20them%20about%20our%20tribe%E2%80%99s%20history%20and%20why%20we%20use%20certain%20ingredients%20the%20way%20we%20do%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Palash%20Mallick%20from%20West%20Bengal%E2%80%99s%20Lodha%20tribe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20happy%20that%20the%20sales%20of%20his%20star%20dish%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Edudh%20puli%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20(rice%20dumplings)%20have%20increased%20over%20the%20years.%20The%20fried%20dumplings%20are%20made%20with%20rice%20flour%2C%20coconut%2C%20jaggery%20and%20milk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20stalls%20away%2C%20Pritesh%20Kumar%20from%20the%20Oraon%20tribe%E2%80%99s%20Khalko%20clan%20excitedly%20narrated%20the%20fascinating%20story%20behind%20each%20dish%20while%20offering%20free%20samples.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20%3Cem%3Ebaas%3C%2Fem%3E%20(bamboo)%20pickle%20is%20good%20for%20your%20blood%2C%20and%20the%3Cem%3E%20demta%20chutney%3C%2Fem%3E%20made%20from%20red%20weaver%20ants%20is%20rich%20in%20protein%20and%20calcium.%20%3Cem%3EJamun%3C%2Fem%3E%20powder%20helps%20control%20sugar%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20the%20potential%20customer%20at%20his%20stall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%202560px)%20100vw%2C%202560px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FIMG_0958_11zon-1710505545-scaled.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%222560%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22For%20these%20chefs%20from%20the%20tribal%20community%2C%20their%20role%20goes%20beyond%20cooking%20and%20showcasing%20their%20food%3B%20it%20is%20a%20way%20to%20connect%20their%20community%20with%20the%20outside%20world.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FIMG_0958_11zon-1710505545-scaled.jpg%202560w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FIMG_0958_11zon-1710505545-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FIMG_0958_11zon-1710505545-500x281.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FIMG_0958_11zon-1710505545-768x432.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FIMG_0958_11zon-1710505545-1536x864.jpg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FIMG_0958_11zon-1710505545-2048x1152.jpg%202048w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FIMG_0958_11zon-1710505545-150x84.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-344985%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EFor%20these%20home%20chefs%2C%20their%20role%20goes%20beyond%20cooking%20and%20showcasing%20their%20food%3B%20it%20is%20a%20way%20to%20connect%20their%20community%20with%20the%20outside%20world.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20how%20cuisine%20helps%20uplift%20his%20community%2C%20Pritesh%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20get%20to%20tell%20our%20stories%20through%20cuisine%20by%20shedding%20light%20on%20ingredients%2C%20preparation%20methods%2C%20taste%20and%20more.%20Get%20us%20more%20stalls%20like%20these.%20We%20will%20not%20only%20survive%20but%20also%20flourish.%20We%20offer%20foods%20that%20may%20not%20be%20available%20everywhere%20in%20India.%20Every%20generation%20closely%20guards%20these%20recipes.%20It%20is%20our%20fourth%20time%20here%20%5Bat%20the%20conclave%5D.%20Every%20year%2C%20we%20receive%20orders%20from%20across%20India%20once%20we%20go%20back%20home.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMentioning%20the%20controversial%20plant%20of%20%3Cem%3Emahua%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3E(Madhuca%20longifolia)%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20he%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EMahua%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20unfortunately%20only%20popular%20as%20an%20alcoholic%20drink%20and%20hence%20people%20assume%20our%20community%20is%20backwards%20due%20to%20this.%20What%20many%20people%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20is%20that%20%3Cem%3Emahua%3C%2Fem%3E%20can%20be%20used%20to%20make%20pickles%20and%20cookies%20as%20well.%20They%20have%20several%20health%20benefits.%20We%20aim%20to%20bring%20these%20dishes%20into%20the%20mainstream.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPritesh%20and%20his%20family%20earn%20five%20months%E2%80%99%20worth%20of%20earnings%20within%20two%20days%20at%20Samvaad.%20He%20expressed%20hope%20that%20future%20generations%20will%20be%20eager%20to%20learn%20these%20recipes%20now%20due%20to%20its%20increasing%20market%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeeta%20Sandil%20of%20the%20Munda%20tribe%2C%20who%20was%20participating%20in%20the%20conclave%20for%20the%20second%20time%2C%20said%20she%20had%20seen%20similar%20profits%20because%20of%20Samvaad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20thought%20we%20were%20the%20only%20ones%2C%20but%20I%20was%20pleasantly%20surprised%20to%20see%20so%20many%20tribal%20communities.%20We%20sold%20a%20lot%20last%20year%2C%20so%20we%20are%20back%20with%20several%20new%20additions%20like%20chicken%20%3Cem%3Ekhichdi%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20duck%20meat%2C%20%3Cem%3Edhuska%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Emasoor%20dal%20pakoda%3C%2Fem%3E%20(lentil%20fritters)%20and%20%3Cem%3Ekhasi%20%3C%2Fem%3Epieces%20(goat%20legs).%20These%20dishes%20are%20good%20for%20bones%2C%20kidney%20stones%2C%20heart%20and%20gut.%20We%20prepare%20all%20the%20spices%20at%20home%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20told%3Cstrong%3E%20The%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeeing%20the%20positive%20response%20here%2C%20Geeta%20expressed%20her%20desire%20to%20quit%20her%20restaurant%20job%20and%20start%20her%20own%20food%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESamvaad%20is%20helping%20participants%20like%20Geeta%20who%20wish%20to%20walk%20on%20the%20entrepreneurial%20road.%20For%20instance%2C%20this%20year%2C%20it%20tied%20up%20with%20Zomato%20to%20home-deliver%20traditional%20cuisines%20prepared%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F344574%2Ftata-samvaad-tribal-conclave-preserves-lost-heritage-artisans-sell-handicrafts%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eat%20the%20conclave%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20Jamshedpur%20for%20five%20days!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20not%20all%2C%20tribal%20cuisine%20has%20been%20taking%20over%20luxury%20dining%20tables%2C%20as%20TSF%20collaborated%20with%20Indian%20Hotels%20Company%20Limited%20(IHCL)%20to%20put%20up%20food%20carnivals%20and%20workshops%20at%20the%20Taj%20chain%20of%20hotels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Edited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3B%20All%20photos%20courtesy%3A%20Gopi%20Karelia)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710506256000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FIMG_0960_11zon-1710505353-scaled.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D344924%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Tata%20Samvaad%2C%20a%20tribal%20conclave%20in%20Jamshedpur%20by%20the%20Tata%20Steel%20Foundation%2C%20showcased%20diverse%20indigenous%20cuisines%20from%2035%20tribes.%20Around%20140%20home%20chefs%20shared%20unique%20dishes%20like%20ragi%20samosa%2C%20demta%20chutney%2C%20dudh%20puli%2C%20etc%2C%20highlighting%20the%20cultural%20significance%20of%20their%20ingredients.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Gopi%20Karelia%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F344924%2Ftata-samvaad-conclave-showcase-tribal-cuisine-dishes-by-home-chefs-entrepreneurs%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Lullabies%20to%20Languages%3A%20Fellowship%20Offers%20Funds%20to%20Help%20Tribal%20Youth%20Preserve%20Generational%20Wisdom%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20has%20been%20published%20in%20partnership%20with%20Samvaad%20%E2%80%93%20Enabled%20by%20Tata%20Steel%20Foundation%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2050%20years%2C%20India%20has%20lost%20over%20250%20languages%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20UNESCO.%20This%20loss%20not%20only%20affects%20languages%20but%20also%20various%20fields%20like%20history%2C%20biology%2C%20and%20anthropology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20good%20news.%20Lately%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20been%20a%20growing%20effort%20to%20preserve%20cultural%20identities%20throughout%20India%2C%20and%20the%20Samvaad%20Fellowship%20programme%20stands%20as%20a%20significant%20contributor%20to%20this%20movement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarted%20in%202017%20to%20empower%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F344574%2Ftata-samvaad-tribal-conclave-preserves-lost-heritage-artisans-sell-handicrafts%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etribal%20communities%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20fellowship%20encourages%20their%20youth%20to%20document%20their%20history%2C%20culture%2C%20ecology%2C%20traditions%2C%20art%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20purpose%20of%20the%20fellowship%20is%20to%20get%20tribal%20communities%20to%20deep%20dive%20into%20their%20culture%20and%20help%20them%20shape%20their%20ideas%20in%20collaboration%20with%20various%20experts.%20The%20idea%20behind%20documenting%20different%20cultures%20is%20to%20create%20a%20repository%20of%20information%20and%20make%20it%20accessible%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%20At%20Samvaad%2C%20being%20a%20tribal%20is%20a%20source%20of%20pride.%20The%20community%20answers%20the%20toughest%20questions%20about%20their%20identity%20and%20tries%20to%20address%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sourav%20Roy%2C%20TSF%20CEO%2C%20told%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fellowship%20is%20part%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F344526%2Fsamvaad-tata-steel-foundation-celebrates-culture-of-tribes-of-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESamvaad%2C%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20tribal%20conclaves%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20country%2C%20enabled%20by%20Tata%20Steel%20Foundation%20(TSF).%20It%20takes%20place%20from%2015%20to%2019%20November%20every%20year%20to%20commemorate%20the%20birth%20anniversary%20of%20Birsa%20Munda%2C%20a%20tribal%20independence%20activist%20and%20leader%20from%20Jharkhand%E2%80%99s%20Munda%20tribe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESamvaad%20stepped%20into%20a%20decadal%20journey%20in%202023%20and%20the%20recent%20edition%E2%80%99s%20theme%20was%20%E2%80%98Walk%20with%20Me%E2%80%99.%20The%20theme%20recognised%20the%20journey%20of%20ideas%2C%20dialogues%2C%20individuals%2C%20and%20collectives%20within%20and%20among%20the%20tribes%20of%20India%2C%20aiming%20to%20address%20future%20challenges%20through%20shared%20wisdom%2C%20idea%20exchange%2C%20and%20self-learning.%20The%20five-day%20conclave%20spotlighted%20various%20solution-driven%20dialogues%20and%20initiatives%20that%20have%20emerged%20from%20past%20conclaves.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20hosted%20at%20five%20locations%20%E2%80%94%20TSF%20Community%20Hall%20(RD%20Bhatta)%2C%20Jamshedpur%20Nature%20Trail%2C%20Tribal%20Cultural%20Centre%2C%20Gopal%20Maidan%2C%20and%20Johar%20Haat.%20Gopal%20Maidan%20and%20Tribal%20Culture%20Centre%20served%20as%20the%20main%20activity%20hubs%20while%20Johar%20Haat%20housed%20a%20cloud%20kitchen%20facility%20for%20preparing%20food%20for%20home%20delivery%20in%20collaboration%20with%20Zomato.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20the%20conclave%20has%20celebrated%20and%20united%20over%2040%2C000%20people%20from%20over%20200%20tribes%20in%20India%20and%2017%20other%20countries.%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20spoke%20to%20past%20fellows%20%E2%80%94%20Banwang%20Losu%20and%20Amabel%20Susngi%20%E2%80%94%20about%20their%20tremendous%20action%20towards%20preserving%20their%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FWancho_language_training_of_teacher_PC_banwang_losu-1710425245.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20fellowship%20aims%20to%20engage%20tribal%20communities%20in%20exploring%20their%20culture%20and%20collaboratively%20shaping%20their%20ideas%20with%20experts.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FWancho_language_training_of_teacher_PC_banwang_losu-1710425245.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FWancho_language_training_of_teacher_PC_banwang_losu-1710425245-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FWancho_language_training_of_teacher_PC_banwang_losu-1710425245-500x281.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FWancho_language_training_of_teacher_PC_banwang_losu-1710425245-768x432.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FWancho_language_training_of_teacher_PC_banwang_losu-1710425245-150x84.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-344889%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20fellowship%20aims%20to%20engage%20tribal%20communities%20in%20exploring%20their%20culture%20and%20collaboratively%20shaping%20their%20ideas%20with%20experts.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EPreserving%20lullabies%20and%20languages%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20centuries%2C%20people%20across%20the%20world%20have%20followed%20the%20nightly%20ritual%20of%20singing%20lullabies%20to%20infants%20for%20a%20peaceful%20sleep.%20Closer%20home%2C%20we%20have%20thousands%20of%20lullabies%20in%20different%20languages.%20However%2C%20this%20tradition%20has%20faded%20over%20the%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsk%20yourself%20whether%20you%20remember%20a%20lullaby%20from%20your%20childhood!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%2028-year-old%20Amabel%20Susngi%20from%20Meghalaya%20observed%20that%20the%20lullabies%20in%20her%20native%20language%20Khasi%20were%20becoming%20a%20thing%20of%20the%20past%2C%20she%20decided%20to%20document%20them.%20As%20part%20of%20the%20Samvaad%20Fellowship%2C%20she%20gathered%20various%20lullabies%20and%20published%20them%20in%20a%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20PhD%20researcher%20and%20a%20singer%2C%20she%20travelled%20across%20Meghalaya%20for%20over%20a%20year%20to%20collect%20these%20lullabies.%20She%20has%20documented%2025%20of%20them%20in%20her%20book%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EHa%20Yupiam%20Ka%20Bei%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20(On%20Mother%E2%80%99s%20Lap)%2C%20which%20was%20published%20in%20both%20Khasi%20and%20English%20this%20year%20at%20Samvaad.%20It%20also%20comes%20with%20musical%20notations%2C%20and%20each%20piece%20has%20a%20QR%20code%20leading%20the%20reader%20to%20its%20YouTube%20version.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20researching%20the%20folk%20music%20of%20the%20Pnar%20community%2C%20I%20realised%20that%20not%20many%20people%20remembered%20lullabies.%20That%20was%20a%20shock.%20Lullabies%20have%20been%20passed%20down%20through%20generations.%20Whether%20traditional%20or%20something%20made%20up%20by%20parents%2C%20it%20has%20been%20an%20important%20fabric%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20culture%2C%E2%80%9D%20Amabel%20told%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20road%20to%20publishing%20had%20its%20challenges%2C%20she%20adds%2C%20the%20biggest%20being%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CParents%20don%E2%80%99t%20sing%20anymore%2C%20and%20elderly%20people%20do%20not%20quite%20remember%20all%20the%20lullabies.%20Some%20knew%20only%20one%20line%20or%20two%2C%20and%20some%20remembered%20only%20the%20tune%20or%20lyrics.%20Scheduling%20meetings%20was%20not%20an%20option%2C%20so%20I%20had%20to%20work%20around%20their%20availability.%20Samvaad%20solved%20the%20critical%20funding%20problem%2C%20and%20it%20helped%20me%20connect%20with%20other%20fellows%20around%20the%20country%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Banwang%20Losu%20from%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20developed%20a%20script%20to%20preserve%20Wancho%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Tibetan-Burman%20language%20spoken%20in%20the%20Longding%20region%20of%20the%20state%20and%20some%20parts%20of%20Myanmar%2C%20Nagaland%2C%20and%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBanwang%20first%20felt%20the%20need%20to%20have%20a%20Wancho%20script%20when%20he%20was%20asked%20to%20collect%20data%20about%20his%20community%20as%20part%20of%20his%20socio-economic%20study%20in%20college.%20He%20was%20unable%20to%20find%20the%20right%20English%20words%20to%20convey%20subtle%20tones.%20He%20tried%20to%20do%20some%20research%20and%20even%20started%20pursuing%20a%20master%E2%80%99s%20in%20linguistics%20at%20Deccan%20College%20Post%20Graduation%20and%20Research%20Institute%20in%20Pune.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20developing%20the%20script%2C%20he%20took%20inspiration%20from%20nature%20and%20Wancho%20cultural%20symbols%2C%20practices%2C%20and%20gestures.%20He%20developed%20a%20script%20with%2044%20letters%20(15%20vowels%20and%2029%20consonants)%2C%20each%20letter%20representing%20a%20distinct%20tone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBanwang%20was%20the%20first%20fellow%20at%20Samvaad.%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20working%20on%20the%20Wancho%20script%2C%20I%20heard%20about%20Samvaad%20and%20came%20here%20in%202017%20without%20any%20proposal.%20However%2C%20the%20jury%20was%20delighted%20to%20see%20my%20work.%20Being%20a%20fellow%20here%20was%20eye-opening%20as%20it%20is%20the%20only%20programme%20for%20tribals%20at%20this%20scale.%20Using%20the%20grant%2C%20I%20made%20textbooks%20on%20the%20Wancho%20language%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBanwang%20taught%20the%20language%20to%202%2C000%20people%2C%20and%2020%20of%20them%20are%20now%20teachers.%20Thanks%20to%20his%20work%2C%20over%206%2C000%20students%20can%20read%20and%20write%20in%20Wancho.%20He%20also%20got%20the%20script%20approved%20for%20online%20use%20by%20the%20US-based%20Unicode%20Consortium.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEvery%20language%20is%20equally%20important%20irrespective%20of%20how%20big%20or%20small.%20We%20have%20to%20look%20at%20other%20minority%20languages%20with%20the%20same%20status%20and%20build%20scripts%20to%20preserve%20them.%20Loss%20of%20language%20is%20a%20loss%20of%20our%20own%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%202560px)%20100vw%2C%202560px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FSourav_Roy_taking_a_session_with_fellowship_applicants_11zon-1710425242-scaled.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%2225